Movie Dataset — Full Analysis Summary
Dataset Overview
Source: IMDB 5000 Movie Dataset (movie_metadata.csv)
Original Size: ~5043 rows, multiple columns
Retained after cleaning: ~77% of rows
Task 1: Data Import & Inspection
Loaded the dataset into a pandas DataFrame called movies
Inspected columns, shapes, and data types to understand the structure
Dataset contains information on movies including budget, gross, IMDb scores, genres, directors, and actors
Task 2: Data Cleaning
Null Value Analysis
Performed column-wise and row-wise null counts
Calculated null percentage per column to identify problematic columns
Columns Dropped (15 total)
Removed irrelevant columns including color, facebook likes for cast, duration, content_rating, country, aspect_ratio, plot_keywords, etc.

Row Cleaning
Dropped rows where high null columns (>5% nulls) had missing values
Dropped rows with more than 5 NaN values
Filled missing language values with 'English'
Result: ~77% of original rows retained
Task 3: Data Analysis
3.1 Unit Conversion
Converted budget and gross columns from dollars → million dollars for readability
3.2 & 3.3 Top 10 Profitable Movies
Created a profit column (gross - budget)
Removed duplicate rows before final ranking
Finding: Two James Cameron movies (Avatar & Titanic) appear in the top 10 most profitable films
3.4 IMDb Top 250
Filtered movies with num_voted_users > 25,000 for credibility
Ranked top 250 by IMDb score
Extracted non-English films into Top_Foreign_Lang_Film
Finding: Indian film Veer-Zaara appears in the top foreign language films list
3.5 Best Directors
Grouped movies by director and calculated mean IMDb score
Finding: Damien Chazelle (Whiplash, La La Land) ranks among the top 10 directors by average IMDb rating
3.6 Popular Genre Combinations
Extracted top 2 genres from the genres column for each movie
Grouped by genre combinations and calculated mean gross revenue
Finding: Family + Sci-Fi is the most profitable genre combination by mean gross
3.7 Critic vs Audience Favorite Actors
Analyzed movies starring Meryl Streep, Leonardo DiCaprio, and Brad Pitt as lead actors
Compared mean num_critic_for_reviews and num_user_for_reviews
Finding: Leonardo DiCaprio leads in both critic reviews and audience reviews
Key Insights
Finding	Detail
Most profitable director	James Cameron (Avatar, Titanic)
Highest rated director	Damien Chazelle
Most profitable genre combo	Family + Sci-Fi
Most reviewed actor (critics)	Leonardo DiCaprio
Most reviewed actor (audience)	Leonardo DiCaprio
Top foreign language film	Veer-Zaara
Data retained after cleaning	~77%
Tools & Libraries Used
Python 3
NumPy — numerical operations
Pandas — data manipulation, grouping, filtering, and aggregation
